<div class="results-box">
  <p class="amount"><strong><%= number_to_currency @calculator.amount_owed, unit: "£", precision: 2 %></strong></p>
  <% if @calculator.amount_owed == 0 %>
    <p>You don’t need to pay back any of your Child Benefit as tax. This is an estimate based on the figures you provided.</p>

  <% else %>
    <p>The person with the highest income has to pay back <%= number_to_currency @calculator.amount_owed, unit: "£", precision: 2 %> (<%= @calculator.percent_tax_charge %>% of the total Child Benefit received). This is an estimate based on the figures you provided.</p>

  <% end %>
</div>


<div class="results-text">
  <p>You only have to pay tax back on Child Benefit received between 7 January and 5 April.</p>

  <h4>Self Assessment deadlines</h4>

  <p>You will have to pay back <%= number_to_currency @calculator.amount_owed, unit: "£", precision: 2 %> from the tax year 2012 to 2013 through Self Assessment. You’ll need to <a href="/register-for-aslf-assessment">register for Self Assessment</a> by 5 October, and complete your tax return in time.

  <p>The deadlines are:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>paper tax returns - by midnight 31 October 2013</li>
    <li>online tax returns - by midnight 31 January 2014</li>
    <li>final payment of any tax due - by midnight 31 January 2014</li>
  </ul>

  <p>You’ll have to <a href="/self-assessment-tax-returns/penalties">pay a penalty</a> if you miss the deadline.</p>

  <h4>What to do next</h4>

  <% if @calculator.amount_owed > 0 && @calculator.starting_children.any? %>
    <p>You’ll need to pay back any tax you already owe through Self Assessment. From now, you can either:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>carry on getting Child Benefit for the year, and pay whatever you owe back as tax</li>
      <li><a href="http://hmrc.gov.uk/childbenefitcharge/stopchbpayments.htm" rel="external">stop getting Child Benefit</a>, and pay whatever you already owe back as tax</li>
    </ul>
  <% else %>
    <p>For the tax year 2013 to 2014, you’ll need to pay back any tax you already owe through Self Assessment. From now, you can either:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>carry on getting Child Benefit for the year, and pay whatever you owe back as tax</li>
      <li><a href="http://hmrc.gov.uk/childbenefitcharge/stopchbpayments.htm" rel="external">stop getting Child Benefit</a></li>
    </ul>
  <% end %>

  <p>Only the person getting Child Benefit can ask for it to be stopped.</p>

  <% if @calculator.amount_owed > 0 && @calculator.starting_children.any? %>

    <h4>New children</h4>

    <p>From now, you can either:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>carry on getting Child Benefit for the year, and pay whatever you owe back as tax</li>
      <li>register the child for Child Benefit and ask for it not to be paid to you</li>
    </ul>

    %**NOTE: need to find out how to do the latter**%
  <% end %>

  <p>Come back to the calculator if your circumstances change.</p>

</div>
